description.narrative: The PDO is to contribute to improving the efficiency and quality of the public health system of the Republic of Serbia through the strengthening of: (i) health financing, purchasing, and maintenance systems; and (ii) quality improvement systems and management of selected priority non-communicable diseases.

condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Accounting software | Description :No later than thirty (30) days after the Effective Date, the Borrower shallcause the PCU to have installed and operational an accounting system and software satisfactory to the Bank. | Due Date :10-Feb-2015

Finance Agreement :PCU Quarterly Meetings | Description :The PCU shall be in charge of organizing quarterly Project review meetingsto be called by the Ministry of Health, and attended by relevant officials of the Ministry of Health, Institute for Public Health,Health Insurance Fund, and key stakeholders. | Frequency :Quarterly

Finance Agreement :Project Coordination Unit | Description :The Borrower shall maintain, throughout Project implementation, the PCUwith terms of reference, staff and resources satisfactory to the Bank. The PCU shall be headed by a senior official of the Ministryof Health. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Project Operations and Grants Manual | Description :The Borrower shall carry out the Project in accordance withthe Project Operations and Grants Manual satisfactory to the Bank. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Project Policy Board | Description :No later than 30 days from the Effective Date, the Borrower shall formallyestablish and shall thereafter maintain, the Project Policy Board, with terms of reference, staff and resources satisfactory to theBank. | Due Date :10-Feb-2015

Finance Agreement :Quality Improvement Agreements | Description :The Borrower shall enter into an agreement with each of theEligible PHC facilities (“Quality Improvement Agreements”), under terms and conditions approved by the Bank and elaborated in theProject Operations and Grants Manual, setting forth the technical, administrative and fiduciary aspects of their participation inthe implementation and use of funds under Part 1(b) of the Project. | Frequency :Yearly
